<subSubSection id="7E4CEEC7823BC7C290574E63CD480BC4" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="9F036A289791CFEF663135E00AB6BD13" pageId="0" pageNumber="77">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="81BF759629CA308A81335369ABE3A882" pageId="0" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicName id="F5D28D1E232129D8FD6FD09E96620F36" authorityName="Kataoka &amp; L. G. Lohmann" authorityYear="2021" class="Gastropoda" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Martinella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Martinella tomentosa" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis id="B2CCD00FEB67F44EC068C0E5A7B7533A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="77">Martinella tomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other Amazonian species of 
<taxonomicName id="B4A4EE5FF8824CDADD43CA67D463BDC9" class="Gastropoda" family="Bignoniaceae" genus="Martinella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Martinella" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="AFCFA269F66A54E2A11CF9F2DEB6AAC6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="77">Martinella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the tomentose leaflets and branches, and inflorescences arranged in thyrses, as opposed to the glabrous to lanuginose leaflets and inflorescences arranged in racemes or lax thyrses of all other Amazonian species.
</paragraph>
<caption id="132F9A5B26FEB8D29E6260ECF258411C" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.177.64465.figure11" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/542007" pageId="0" pageNumber="77" start="Figure 11" startId="F11">
